    "ambiguity_status": "minor",
    "intended": "Let $h(n)$ be minimal such that there is a graph on $n$ vertices with $n+h(n)$ edges which contains a cycle on $k$ vertices, for all $3\\leq k\\leq n$. Estimate $h(n)$. In particular, is it true that\\[h(n) \\geq \\log_2n+\\log_*n-O(1),\\]where $\\log_*n$ is the iterated logarithmic function?",
